    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-12-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">de Aspíoz</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Mexico</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 82.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Most Excellent Sir</hi>: In answer to the note of your
                    Department, No. 543, of the 9th instant, I have the honor to say to you that I
                    have received instructions from my Government to accept the sum of $500 in final
                    settlement and full payment of the claim of the Mexican, Eulogio Zambrano, for
                    damages and denial of justice.</p>
                <p>I communicate this for your information and beg you to accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">M. de Azpíroz.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
